Node.Notes: Uncertain, probably refers to the tune, whose meaning seems to be "dove of silence of distant ones" or (with revocalization) "doves of distant terebiths."
According to 1s21:10-15 and 27:1-4, David went ot Gath (one of the five main Philistine cities) twice to escape from Saul.
Uncertain. Many take as "enemies." Some prefer "watchers/ambushers" while others prefer "slanderers."
Uncertain. Many treat as adverbial accusative "proudly." Others change word to yield "O Most High" and link with next verse.

First half of verse uncertain, with many different proposals. Many accept slight change of word "save" to yield "cast out." LXX reading "on no account will you save them" also popular. Tree assumes rhetorical question: "[Will you] save them on account of their evil?"
Uncertain. Variously related to "tossings/lament/wandering." Only consensus is that it is some kind of distress.
Assumes "deliver" from previous clause or another verb like "keep": "Did you not keep my feet from stumbling?"
